# {{.Command.Name}}

`{{.Command.Name}}` manages disaster recovery for OpenShift and Kubernetes
clusters. When the user asks for help with a `{{.Command.Name}}` task,
read the matching skill file before responding.

The user typically runs `{{.Command.Name}} init` to create a configuration
file. You can help with editing the configuration and running `validate`,
`gather`, and `test` commands.

## Command execution rules

- Run every command in the foreground with enough timeout for it to
  complete. Check the skill for expected duration and set the timeout
  accordingly.
- Never run commands in parallel. Always wait for one command to finish
  before starting another.
- If a command times out or is still running, report to the user and
  wait for instructions. Never kill, stop, or restart a command on your
  own.
